<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>possible :&nbsp;</p>
<p>IN wake of growing nuclear security challenge in India’s nbd. Hence need for revisiting nuclear doctrine.&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Solution :&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>SIPRI, 2021 = increase in nuclear weapons in nbd. China and pak.&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Nuclear journey : U-238 enrichment (1958) , (1974) Pokharan Smiling buddha , NSG formed , (1988?) operation shakti (1st nuke power w/o NPT signing)&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>NPT (50 years in 2020) : iimit escalation of nuclear arms race +&nbsp; complete disarmament&nbsp;</p>
<p>unfair : P5 continue to have nuclear weapons. Divide the world in have and have nots</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>2003 : nuclear doctrine&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>CMD&nbsp; - credible minimum deterrence&nbsp;</li>
<li>NFU - no first use</li>
<li>massive retaliation (second strike capability develop)</li>
<li>no use against non nuclear weapon state</li>
<li>only auth by NCA (civil political leadership)&nbsp;</li>
<li>strict control over nuclear fissile material&nbsp;</li>
<li>commitment to nuclear disarmament&nbsp;</li></ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>YES : revisit nuclear doctrine&nbsp;</p>
<ol>
<li>mere declaratory , not bound by diplomatic arragngement wrt nbd states&nbsp;</li>
<li>Pak - has no nuclear doctrine =&gt; need to improve&nbsp;</li>
<li>proliferation = nuclear power increasing nuclear weapons — further strengthen nuke disarmament&nbsp;</li></ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>NO : don’t revisit</p>
<ol>
<li>China - NFU too.&nbsp;</li>
<li>effective - multiple fights in south asia yet no nuclear escalation happened.&nbsp;</li>
<li>123 agreement - USA india nuclear deal&nbsp;</li></ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>way forward :&nbsp;</p>
<p>mutual dialogue during crisis to ensure no escalation .&nbsp;</p>
<p>pak = NFU adopt&nbsp;</p>
<p>enter NSG = strengthen image as responsible nuclear power.&nbsp;</p>
